Package: pleior
Type: Package
Title: Pleiotropy Analysis for GWAS Data
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
     person("Dany", "Mukesha", , "danymukesha@gmail.com", 
        role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Tool to identifying and analyze pleiotropic genetic variants 
    in genome-wide association studies (GWAS). Pleiotropy occurs when 
    a single genetic variant influences multiple traits, offering insights
    into shared biological pathways and disease relationships. 
    The package includes functions for data loading, preprocessing, 
    pleiotropy detection, and visualization using Manhattan plots.
